SIMPLE: dermoptera
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dermoptera
<hw>Der*mop"te*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>de`rma</grk> skin + <grk>pte`rux</grk> wing.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The division of insects which
includes the earwigs (<fam>Forticulid⟦ae⟧</fam>).</def><-- now usu.
<ord>Dermaptera</ord> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of lemuroid mammals
having a parachutelike web of skin between the fore and hind legs, of
which the colugo (<gen>Galeopithecus</gen>) is the type. See
<er>Colugo</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of Mammalia; the
<er>Chiroptera</er>.</def></p>

<p><altsp>[Written also <asp>Dermaptera</asp>, and
<asp>Dermatoptera</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dermopteran</ent>⟦br⟧
